Okay, Harry, a reusable data table is a cornerstone of any admin dashboard! Let's build a `DataTable` component that's clean, striped, and handles those awkward empty states.

We'll make it accept two main props: `data` (your array of objects) and `columns` (to define your headers and how to extract data for each column).

Here’s the component:

```jsx
// src/components/DataTable.jsx
import React from 'react';

const DataTable = ({ data, columns }) => {
  // Graceful handling for no data or no columns defined
  if (!data || data.length === 0) {
    return (
      <div className="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md text-center text-gray-500">
        <p className="text-lg font-medium">No data available.</p>
        <p className="text-sm">Please check your data source or try again later.</p>
      </div>
    );
  }

  if (!columns || columns.length === 0) {
    return (
      <div className="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md text-center text-red-500">
        <p className="text-lg font-medium">Error: No columns defined for the table.</p>
        <p className="text-sm">Please provide a `columns` prop with header and accessor definitions.</p>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <div className="overflow-x-auto bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md">
      <table className="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200">
        <thead className="bg-gray-50">
          <tr>
            {columns.map((col, index) => (
              <th
                key={col.accessor || index} // Use accessor as key if available, otherwise index
                scope="col"
                className="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider"
              >
                {col.header}
              </th>
            ))}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody className="bg-white divide-y divide-gray-200">
          {data.map((row, rowIndex) => (
            <tr key={rowIndex} className={rowIndex % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-white' : 'bg-gray-50'}>
              {columns.map((col, colIndex) => (
                <td
                  key={col.accessor || colIndex}
                  className="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-gray-900"
                >
                  {/* Access the data using the accessor */}
                  {row[col.accessor]}
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  );
};

export default DataTable;
```

**How to use it (e.g., in your `AdminLayout` or a new dashboard page):**

```jsx
