The code is causing an infinite loop because `data` is included in the dependency array. When `fetchUser` finishes, it calls `setData(data)`. This changes the `data` state, which triggers the `useEffect` to run again, fetching the data again, updating the state again, infinitely.

To fix this, we should remove `data` from the dependency array and only include `id` so it only refetches if the user ID changes. Here is the corrected code:

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  fetchUser(id).then(setData);
}, [id]); // Only re-run the effect if the 'id' changes
```
